	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, May 6th 10:44 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=32254><span id= >Nixoh</span></a><br><span id=notbold>432 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.45]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&quot;[Verant] put all this effort into [Legends], and then do nothing for the current servers [and] raise the subscription prices&quot;<br><br>Well, let's see:<br><br>* Subscription price didn't raise for years<br>* SoL goodies available even if you didn't buy SoL<br>* New CT with insanely good 55+ group exp/loot<br>* Caster revamp (what mid-level cleric can complain)<br>* No spellbook pre-35 and hell levels gone<br>* GM events still continue just as commonly<br><br>Now, I'm the first to whine about things like the delay on the new UI, delay on the bazaar, etc. But, let's be fair: Verant does give us our money's worth for the cost of a couple McDonald's meals per month. I feel bad for folks like the guilds that took Seru and the Emp, who got crappy loot for the time spent. But, I think that the low-to-mid-to-high end game (but not &quot;end game&quot;) are very reasonable and well maintained. I have a wish-list and if Verant starts slacking off I'll be the first in line to slap them. But, adding Legends was a good move, and it does make sense to have a premium service.<br><br>Note: I don't play on Legends because I play with RL friends who aren't going to spend $40/m on this game, so don't think I'm saying &quot;I like what I've got, and you can rot on the back-water servers.&quot;<br></p>&nbsp;<br>You gain experience!<br>The Goblin Warlord hits YOU for 50 points!<br></td></td></tr>
